com.google.gcloud.datastore

Class StructuredQuery<V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.google.gcloud.datastore.Query<V>
      • com.google.gcloud.datastore.StructuredQuery<V>
  • Type Parameters:
    V - the type of the result values this query will produce
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    StructuredQuery.KeyOnlyQuery, StructuredQuery.ProjectionQuery

    public class StructuredQuery<V>
extends Query<V>
    An implementation of a Google Cloud Datastore Query that can be constructed by providing all the specific query elements.

    A usage example:

    A simple query that returns all entities for a specific kind 

     StructuredQuery<Entity> query = StructuredQuery.builder().kind(kind).build();
   QueryResult<Entity> results = datastore.run(query);
   while (results.hasNext()) {
     Entity entity = results.next();
     ...
   }

    A less trivial example of a projection query that returns the first 10 results of "age" and "name" properties (sorted and grouped by "age") with an age greater than 18 

     StructuredQuery<ProjectionEntity> query = StructuredQuery.projectionBuilder()
       .kind(kind)
       .projection(Projection.property("age"), Projection.first("name"))
       .filter(PropertyFilter.gt("age", 18))
       .groupBy("age")
       .orderBy(OrderBy.asc("age"))
       .limit(10)
       .build();
   QueryResult<ProjectionEntity> results = datastore.run(query);
   ...
    See Also:
    Datastore queries, Serialized Form
